LG Electronics Advances in Seoul Trading, BNP Paribas Raises Stock Rating

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-03-28T00:22:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/lg-electronics-advances-in-seoul-trading-bnp-paribas-raises-stock-rating.html
LG Electronics Inc. (066570)  advanced in
Seoul trading after BNP Paribas raised its stock rating to
“buy” from “reduce,” saying a recovery in its handset
business will drive earnings growth and boost its share price.
The world’s third-largest mobile-phone maker gained 2.8 percent
to 109,000 won as of 9:18 a.m. on the Korea Exchange. The
benchmark Kospi stock index rose 0.2 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
 sshin15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
